---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Ankush Dhankhar" description="About Ankush Dhankhar Lorem Ipsum">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			<Hero
				title="About"
				tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
			>
			<div class="aboutimg">
				<img
					width="430"
					src="/assets/about2.jpg"
					alt="Ankush Dhankhar at work with a colleague"
				/>
			</div>
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background </h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>I am currently pursuing a B.Tech degree in Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence at <a href="http://nsut.ac.in/">NSUT</a>( Netaji Subhas University of Technology, Dwarka, Delhi ). With a strong foundation in computer science principles and a keen interest in solving real-life problems through technology, I have developed a diverse portfolio of applications and projects. My education includes schooling at <a href="https://www.rpsrewari.edu.in/">RPS </a> Public School in Rewari, Haryana, and <a href="https://opgworldschool.com/dwarka">OPG World School</a>  in Dwarka, Delhi.
					</p><br>
					<p>My technical expertise spans programming languages such as Kotlin and JavaScript, and frameworks and libraries like Jetpack Compose and Coroutines. I am proficient in databases including Room Database and Firebase, and skilled in development tools such as Android Studio and Git. Some of the projects I have worked on include <a href="https://www.indicwire.com/">Indic Wire</a>, a news website built using Astro and JavaScript, featuring the 'FlipFlop' card to present different perspectives on the same topic; a movie app that provides detailed information about movies using Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, Coroutines, and Firebase; a notes app that allows users to store and manage notes locally with timestamp features; and a bill-splitting app that calculates the amount per person, including tips, using Kotlin, Jetpack Compose, and Coroutines.
                    </p><br>
					<p>In my professional experience as a frontend web developer, I have developed responsive and dynamic web applications, improving user experience and functionality. I am adept at problem-solving, analyzing and resolving complex technical issues, and I work effectively in team settings, contributing to successful project outcomes. Additionally, I am a gaming enthusiast, which enhances my strategic thinking and problem-solving skills. I am dedicated to continuous learning and staying updated with the latest technologies and trends in the software engineering field, positioning myself as a promising software engineer ready to tackle challenging and innovative projects.
                    </p>
				</div>
			</section>
